<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 9:24PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Alamance and
western Orange Counties through 1015 PM EDT...
At 924 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Burlington, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Burlington, Graham, Hillsborough, Mebane, Gibsonville, Haw River,
Swepsonville, Efland, Lake Burlington and Lake Cammack Park &amp; Marina.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
